         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Single Party Framework for ADR Driver and Safety Advisor Examination Schemes and Management of Approved Training Providers</P>
            </TITLE>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="80500000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>The Health and Safety Authority invites expressions of interest for the provision of the management of the ADR driver and safety adviser (DGSA) (road) examination schemes and the approval of driver training courses (hereinafter called ADR and Related Services). The Authority wishes to establish a single party framework agreement.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL CURRENCY="EUR">2000000.00</VAL_ESTIMATED_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80510000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80520000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80521000"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <CPV_ADDITIONAL>
                  <CPV_CODE CODE="80531100"/>
               </CPV_ADDITIONAL>
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="IE"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>Various locations throughout Ireland.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>The Health and Safety Authority invites expressions of interest for the provision of the management of the ADR driver and safety adviser (DGSA) (road) examination schemes and the approval of driver training courses (hereinafter called ADR and Related Services). The Authority wishes to establish a single party framework agreement for the following:</P>
                  <P>(i) the ADR driver examination scheme: maintain and develop the current examination question bank, set and mark examinations and award vocational driver training certificates to qualifying candidates as drivers of vehicles carrying dangerous goods;</P>
                  <P>(ii) the safety adviser examination scheme: maintain and develop the current examination question bank, set and mark examinations and award vocational training certificates to qualifying candidates as safety advisers for the carriage of dangerous goods by road;</P>
                  <P>(iii) the approval of training courses and the appointment of training providers for the training of drivers of dangerous goods vehicles: maintain and develop the current driver training syllabus and standards for training providers (ATP Guidelines), carry out initial and annual re-assessments of course materials and training providers.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <AC_PROCUREMENT_DOC/>
               <VAL_OBJECT CURRENCY="EUR">2000000.00</VAL_OBJECT>
               <DURATION TYPE="MONTH">60</DURATION>
               <NO_RENEWAL/>
               <NB_ENVISAGED_CANDIDATE>5</NB_ENVISAGED_CANDIDATE>
               <CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
                  <P>Based on responses to the qualification criteria the Authority anticipates inviting the top 5 scoring candidates to the dialogue stage, subject to that number qualifying.</P>
               </CRITERIA_CANDIDATE>
               <ACCEPTED_VARIANTS/>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
